A six-year-old girl has been swept away in Tongaat, KwaZulu-Natal. It’s believed the grade one pupil had been trying to cross a river. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - A six-year-old girl has been swept away in Tongaat, KwaZulu-Natal. It’s believed the grade one pupil had been trying to cross a river. READ: Mamelodi residents counting the cost of devastating floods Heavy rains have caused rivers to swell in parts of the province. IPSS Rescue Care and the SAPS Search and Rescue Unit are assisting in looking for the child.